content.description: Challenging start leads to pretty smooth climbing for the rest of the route. Be aware of potential loose blocks up high. Route needs to be cleaned
content.location: Left most route on the wall

content.description: 6 bolts to bolted anchor under a big roof. This is the right route under the roof.  Interesting moves for the first 3 bolts lead to easier climbing.
content.location: Scramble down to the right next to pinnacle rock. Turn right and walk for about  10 minutes through a hallway created by a massive pillar leaning on the main cliffline. This route is located under a massive roof.

content.description: Just left of Womb Life this gorgeous climb is only downgraded by the inconsistency of it’s difficulty.  Begin on flowy 5.11 climbing through rust and tan rock finding slots and slopers to move up to a no-hands stance.  From the ledge get ready and ratchet up the intensity to crimp out of the thin crux which leads to more phenomenal 5.11 secret slot climbing and a beautiful anchor view.
content.location: On the beautiful white/orange wall climbers left of WombLife

content.description: Begin on moderate climbing over excellent quality rock until you reach a good rest about halfway up.  From here the route gets a bit steeper and more exciting.  Search out the good holds and don't get pumped on your way to the chains.
content.location: Two routes climber's left of the giant hueco route (WombLife).  Starts about 8 feet right of an obvious crack.

content.description:
This route is full of variety, with a technical and compression arete down low, a juggy mid-section, and hero roof climbing up high! A very fun route, get on it!

 There are two chain draws on the route to make cleaning a little easier.
content.location: This route climbs out the center of the cave, through the seam and corner system up high

content.description: Closed project, please do not climb
content.location: Center line that starts on the beautiful white face and climbs straight and right out the roof
Climbs middle of overhang past the Froopy Land slabs

content.description: Ground up first ascent. Use a stick clip for the first bolt. This is the major weakness on the left side of a cool overhanging wall. Climb up to a ledge, then pull out onto the face using amazing jug pockets. A big throw gets you to a ledge and the rest. Reach right to clip a bolt. Another bolt will be added to this section, but it is still possible to climb without it. A #6 is advisable until another bolt is added. Make the steep and difficult jamming moves to find the sewer pickle inside the crack. Get to the ledge and enjoy the chimney rest. Move right slightly onto the face and continue up the groove to a set of anchors.
content.protection: Bolts, optional #6 camalot. Will be updated with an extra bolt.
content.location: Look for the overhanging left facing dihedral.

content.description: A big move from the start gives a taste of what's to come.  Ascend through long moves with great holds to a decent rest before venturing into the steeps.  Break right into the over hang, then back left on enormous jugs into near horizontal terrain.  An extremely committing but fun, party-trick boulder guards the exit and the anchors.
content.location: Middle Right of the Melungeon cave.  Starts off of a boulder and moves through big inviting hueco pockets near the first bolt.

content.description:
Closed project please do not climb. 

 Climbs through the roof on the right side through the seam weaknesses. Beautiful enjoyable climbing above the roof to the top of the cliff-line. Great view!
content.location: Left of "Froop there is is" under the giant Pinnacle roof

content.description:
Begin on vertical terrain up to the steepness (trickier than it looks).  Start grabbing jugs.  Keep grabbing jugs.  Get to the jug rail and grab it.  Then ride that jug rail up to more jugs.  Pull the lip to grab some more jugs,  You're almost to the chains.  Hopefully the last few holds are jugs....

 (Think about back-cleaning the 5th bolt to reduce drag)
content.location: Furthest left route in the cave.

content.description: Steep and Hard, to steep and really steep.
content.location: Walk out of the froopy land tunnel and follow the cliff into the cave.  This route is left of the cave before WombLife

content.description: Climbs straight in to a good crux mid way then skirts around to the right side of the upper bulge with an amazing side pull. Get to the top and enjoy the view
content.location: Starts left of the obvious crack left of Spirit Blade.

content.description: A few face climb moves lead to a mantle at a ledge.  From there grab an enormous jug and do a huge high step to a cool pod.  A few more face moves leads to another mantle.  Good moves, but very inconsistent.
content.location: Walk around the corner from Brain Storm arete.  Middle of the wall before the shorty 5.6's

content.description: 4 Bolts to a bolted anchor
content.location: Scramble down to the right of pinnacle rock.  Follow the main cliffline keeping it on your right for 10-15 minutes.  Go through a hallway of rock and under a couple roofs to a short face with this route and the pawn on it.

content.description: A decent route for the grade with a really unfortunate start for the grade.  A large rock stack is the only way to make getting into this route 5.7.  Once on the first little ledge climb right trending movement through decent holds and excellent feet.
content.location: Just up the hill from Spirit Blade, before heading back down hill towards Dominion.

content.description: 6 bolts up a slightly overhanging face. This route is located just climber's left of a large roof with two sport routes under it. Climb up an interested low crux to big jugs and big moves for the rest of the route. Great quality rock climbing!
content.location: Scramble down to the right next to pinnacle rock. Turn right and walk for about 5 minutes through a hallway created by a massive pillar leaning on the main cliffline.

content.description: Begin off the boulder and step over onto the wall and follow blobby slopey laybacks into a bouldery finish.
content.location: Left of Domminion starting on top of the boulder.

content.description: Begin on easy climbing that moves through a large hueco cavity.  After the cavity you will meet a crux to make your brain think "Are there really only slopers here"?
content.location: On the face Right of the arete (brain storm) and left of the big cave (Melungeon).

content.description: Begin on the right side of the arete on a short rock stack to pull past the undercut.  Work your way up through interesting holds and fun movement for the grade.  Don't get caught day dreaming as you try to get to the chains.
content.location: Beautiful ruffled arete just past the super steep cave containing melungeon

content.description: 5 bolts to a bolted anchor under a big roof. This is the left route under the roof. Climb up interesting moves through a flake for the first 3 bolts then enjoy easy climbing to the anchor.
content.location: Scramble down to the right next to pinnacle rock. Turn right and walk for about 5 minutes through a hallway created by a massive pillar leaning on the main cliffline.

content.description: Consistent and cool face climbing on iron rails, buckets and slopers.
content.location: First route around the corner from the Brain Storm Arete

climbs.name: Bambini
climbs.fa: Alesha Reardon, Jack Reardon, Kenneth Fluty

content.description: 35 ft. Short beginners gear line on left side arete... likely the best out of the three short beginner lines on this mini wall.  FA was two 6 year olds!
content.location: Left side of very short wall.

content.description: This climb is as good as it looks from the ground.  Start with a tricky move stepping off the boulder to gain the first ledge. Fun moves lead to a standing rest before the steepness.  The next move will be likely be easier if you have arms the length of a giraffe's neck, otherwise it'll feel hard.  Trend left out of the hueco into excellent face climbing with beautiful exposure.
content.location: This is the route that goest through the enourmous hueco left of the cave.
